page.title: 01GENERAL DESCRIPTION
page.content: The area of the block covers a part of the village of Sutton Bridge known as Wingland. This includes the bridge,the lighthouses and the major trunk road through the village. The area is very flat,in fact, most of it is under sea level. Banks have been built to hold back the River Nene, and the land has been reclaimed fromthe sea. Sutton Bridge is at the junction of the River Nene and the A17 trunk road and was once thought to be an ideal site for a port.Time hasprovedthis to be afalse premise and the village has quietened down to normal tranquility.
